Health department confirms case of child under 5 with acute hepatitis in Puerto Rico
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Department of Health (DH) of Puerto Rico confirmed today, Friday [6 May 2022], that a case of a child under 5 years of age with acute hepatitis is being treated in Puerto Rico. The WHO had warned since last week about rare cases of children with hepatitis of unknown origin in several European countries and in the USA.

The WHO assured last week that the increase in cases of acute childhood hepatitis of unknown origin is a "very urgent" issue to which they are giving "absolute priority." "It is very urgent and we are giving this absolute priority and working very closely with the European Center for Disease Prevention and Control in management and coordination," said WHO Regional Director of Emergencies Gerald Rockenschaub.

